---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '~/components/PageHero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout routeKey="provablyFair">
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Education"
    title="Provably fair, explained"
    subtitle="A 4-minute crash course in how the best crypto casinos prove they cannot rig a result, plus links to the verifier you can run yourself."
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="pf-intro card">
        <p>
          Provably fair gambling is a cryptographic guarantee that the casino cannot
          change the outcome of a bet after seeing it. It does <strong>not</strong>
          guarantee the casino is honest about its bankroll, its withdrawal queue or
          its bonus terms - but it does prove that the dice, the deal or the spin you
          just played out was sealed before you placed the bet.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="pf-steps">
        <article class="pf-step card">
          <div class="pf-num">1</div>
          <h3>The casino commits</h3>
          <p>
            Before your session starts, the casino generates a server seed and
            publishes its SHA256 hash. The hash is a one-way fingerprint - the casino
            cannot change the seed without changing the hash you already saw.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="pf-step card">
          <div class="pf-num">2</div>
          <h3>You contribute entropy</h3>
          <p>
            You generate or modify a client seed. Because the round result is a
            function of both seeds, the casino cannot predict the outcome any better
            than you can - and you cannot predict it any better than they can.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="pf-step card">
          <div class="pf-num">3</div>
          <h3>The round is rolled</h3>
          <p>
            HMAC-SHA256 of the (server seed, client seed, nonce) triple produces a
            deterministic hash. The first few bytes are folded into a number in the
            range each game requires - 0 to 99.99 for dice, 0 to 1 for crash, etc.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="pf-step card">
          <div class="pf-num">4</div>
          <h3>You verify after the fact</h3>
          <p>
            When you rotate the server seed, the casino reveals the original
            unhashed seed. You SHA256 it, confirm it matches the hash you saw at the
            start, then re-roll every round in our
            <a href="/seed-analyzer/">seed analyzer</a> to make sure the casino did
            not lie about the result.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>

      <div class="card pf-tldr">
        <h2>TL;DR</h2>
        <p>
          If the unhashed seed the casino reveals matches the hash they showed at the
          start, and our verifier produces the same roll the casino displayed, the
          round was fair. If either check fails, the casino was caught.
        </p>
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/seed-analyzer/">Open the seed analyzer</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .pf-intro {
    margin-bottom: 32px;
    padding: 28px;
    border-color: rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.32);
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.1), rgba(20, 184, 166, 0.04));
  }
  .pf-intro p {
    font-size: 17px;
    color: var(--color-text-soft);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .pf-intro strong {
    color: #fff;
  }
  .pf-steps {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }
  @media (min-width: 720px) {
    .pf-steps {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }
  .pf-step {
    position: relative;
    padding-top: 28px;
  }
  .pf-num {
    position: absolute;
    top: -16px;
    left: 22px;
    width: 36px;
    height: 36px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #6d28d9);
    color: #fff;
    font-weight: 800;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    box-shadow: 0 6px 14px rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.4);
  }
  .pf-step h3 {
    font-size: 17px;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .pf-step p {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .pf-step a {
    color: var(--color-primary-soft);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .pf-tldr {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 36px;
    border-color: rgba(20, 184, 166, 0.32);
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(20, 184, 166, 0.08), rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.04));
  }
  .pf-tldr h2 {
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .pf-tldr p {
    color: var(--color-text-soft);
    margin-bottom: 22px;
    max-width: 560px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }
</style>
